- Sat 19 Oct 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/c4d85e9e5166/situation-pidmiologique-du-19-octobre-2019?e=e838b4d57b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 18 Oct 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3235, of which 3119 confirmed and 116 probable. In total, there were 2165 deaths (2049 confirmed and 116 probable) and 1042 people cured;
- 478 suspected cases under investigation;
- 2 new confirmed cases in Ituri, including 1 in Mambasa and 1 in Mandima;
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including: 1 community death in Ituri in Mandima; 2 deaths confirmed at the North Kivu ETC in Mabalako;
- 3 new recoveries released from the North Kivu ETC in Mabalako;
- no health workers are among the newly confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 161 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
Organization of a press conference Sat 19 Oct 2019 on the epidemiological situation in the Mutwanga Health Zone. 45 days without a confirmed case of EVD in Mutwanga, North Kivu
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- The sub-coordination of Ebola virus disease (EVD) response in the Mutwanga Health Zone in North Kivu, Dr Tresor Katanga, organized a press conference on Sat 19 Oct 2019 on the epidemiological situation of the Mutwanga Health Zone;
- during this press conference Dr Katanga, Ebola virus disease (EVD) Epidemic Response Coordinator in Mutwanga, reported that this health zone is already in its 45 days without a new confirmed case of EVD. "This denotes the community's commitment to the activities of the response. But reaching or exceeding the threshold of twice 21 days, that is 42 days, does not mean the end of the epidemic," he said;
- he announced that Mutwanga's sub-coordination is preparing to launch community watch activities and that for the moment Community Relays are raising awareness on visitor management;
- he also announced that the Kasindi laboratory, under construction, will soon be operational to address the distance problem between Kasindi and Beni. In addition, the Kasindi Transit Center continues to operate, even without any confirmed case of EVD;
- as for the Ebola orphans, he said they are being cared for by UNICEF. This United Nations organization ensures their schooling and supports their food;
- the same Sat 19 Oct 2019, there was the 1st press conference in Biakato in Mandima. This press conference marks the commitment of radios from the health zones of Mabalako in North Kivu and Mandima in Ituri to get involved in raising awareness of the population in view of its participation in the activities of the fight against the epidemic of EVD.

Interministerial meeting between the Kinshasa joint delegation, the General Coordination of the response, and the interim Governor of the province of North Kivu
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- The interim governor of the province of North Kivu ad interim, the provincial minister of the interior of this province, presided on Fri 18 Oct 2019 in Goma, a meeting between the general coordination of the response, a mixed delegation coming from Kinshasa composed of some members of the Multisectoral Technical Committee for the Ebola Virus Disease Epidemic (CMRE/ST), the State Protocol, and the African Union (AU), as well as the provincial political and health authorities;
- the meeting focused on preparations for the inter-ministerial meeting to be held in Goma on Mon 21 Oct 2019, which requires active participation and ownership of the activity with the provincial authorities for an optimal outcome on the organizational, protocol, and security aspects;
- for this purpose, the representative of CMRE/ST, Prof Michel Kaswa, indicated that the interministerial meeting is part of the response to the epidemic at #MVE and the will of the Head of State, President Felix-Antoine Tshisekedi Tshilombo, to put an early end to this 10th epidemic in the provinces of North and South Kivu and Ituri, in the Democratic Republic of the Congo;
- the representative of the African Union (AU) in the DRC, for his part, said that the Congolese Government, in collaboration with WHO and its institution, will organize this meeting of framework of cross-border collaboration between the ministers of the health of 9 countries in the region, of which the DRC will be a part;
- it is worth noting that in addition to bilateral meetings with some neighboring countries, including Rwanda, Burundi, and Uganda, and with the last visit to the DRC of the AU Commissioner for Social Affairs, the intense mobility of populations and the high risk of regional spread justify the establishment of a framework for collaboration and fruitful information exchange on the movement of people and goods, in order to anticipate the response on the operational readiness aspects of neighboring countries. and surrounding areas of outbreaks;
- this meeting will have the participation of several personalities both national and international.

Vaccination
-----------
- The vaccination of taxi motorcyclists started in the sub-coordinations of Butembo, Beni, Mangina in Mabalako in North Kivu and Mambasa in Ituri;
- 2 expanded vaccination rings were opened, one in the Mambabeka Health Area in Oicha, North Kivu and the other in the Brazza Health Area in Mambasa, Ituri, around the confirmed case of 17 Oct 2019;
- continued immunization of newly recruited frontline staff (PPL) in Kyondo Health Zone (HGR Kyondo) and Kayna Health Area (Bulinda Health Area), Musienene (Kimbulu Reference Health Center), and Butembo (Vulindi Health Area);
- since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 240 494 people have been vaccinated;
- the only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 20 May 2018.

Monitoring at entry points
--------------------------
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of travelers checked (temperature measurement) at the sanitary control points is 107 738 047;
- to date, a total of 111 entry points (PoE) and sanitary control points (PoCs) have been set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri to protect the country's major cities and prevent the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

