- Fri 21 Oct 2019. Congo DR (Beni): attacks condemned
[Radio Okapi; in French, machine trans. edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/10/21/actualite/sante/beni-le-comite-dappui-la-riposte-contre-ebola-condamne-les-attaques

The Ebola Response Support Committee (CAR) condemns attacks on health facilities and response teams last week in Lwemba in Babila-Babombi chiefdom in Mambasa territory in the province of Ituri.

Mr. Omar Kavota fears that this situation will increase the rate of contamination in the neighboring province of North Kivu where the epidemiological situation already seemed to be mastered with a significant decrease in new cases.

"At the level of the CAR, we believe that what is being observed in these days in Lwemba around Biakato may affect, if you do not pay attention, the neighboring province of North Kivu. And so we encourage communities, armed groups, young people in this part of the country to consider that we can defeat Ebola only through responsible behavior. The good practices that have been observed in Mangina, Beni and Katwa have led today to significantly reduce the rate of Ebola contamination", said Omar Kavota.

He calls the inhabitants of Mangina to more responsibility.

