[5] Research:
Date: October 2019
Source: Eurosurveillance [edited]
https://www.eurosurveillance.org/content/10.2807/1560-7917.ES.2019.24.42.1900588


ref: Mizumoto K, Tariq A, Roosa K, et al. Spatial variability in the reproduction number of Ebola virus disease, Democratic Republic of the Congo, January-September 2019. Euro Surveill. 2019; 24(42): pii=1900588; received: 22 Sep 2019; accepted: 17 Oct 2019

Abstract. The ongoing Ebola virus disease epidemic (August 2018 -- October 2019) in the DRC, has been exacerbated by deliberate attacks on healthcare workers despite vaccination efforts. Using a mathematical/statistical modeling framework, we present the quantified effective reproduction number (Rt) at national and regional levels as at 29 Sep 2019. The weekly trend in Rt displays fluctuations while our recent national-level Rt falls slightly above 1.0 with substantial uncertainty, which suggests improvements in epidemic control.

